    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 27-SI SERIES, TYPE 200 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - INSULATED SCREW CHECKS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSULATED SCREW CHECKS</title>
        <para>Carefully inspect the regulator and brush holder mounting screws as shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801508">Figure 8</hotlnk>. Note that on negative ground systems two insulated and one
            grounded screw are used. Damaged or missing insulators can cause damage to electrical components and
            improper charge to the battery.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801508" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801508" filename="../figg08/G0801508.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Inside View of End Frame Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BRUSH HOLDER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. INSULATED SCREWS (2)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. REGULATOR</callout1>
                <callout1>4. LEAD</callout1>
                <callout1>5. DIODE TRIO</callout1>
                <callout1>6. ATTACHING NUTS</callout1>
                <callout1>7. RECTIFIER BRIDGE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
